OMG this weekened has been soooo busy it's not even funny!! Saturday was great!! I went to barrett and had an ok time but boy does Swimming around in a float tube kill. we didn't catch much, and my dad was real shicked about that one. Becasue he has always told me if you can't catch a fish at a lake go to barrett and you will catch at least one gaurenteed!! well, he was right i caught a fish.... but it wasn't a bass. I was bummed. :o( but the one I caught was  huge  for a bluegill. it was about 1 to 2 pounds more on the 2 side and for those fish that is pretty good! I guess.. :Op but anyways then i came home and went straight to MT. Helix and was crewing till 11 then came home. Sunday I worked from 9-3 sooo easy!!! then had my friend ashley pick me up at work because my truck was getting an exhaust on it... which by the way i'm sooo excited!!! :o) I didn't get a loud on though because it's only a ford Ranger and would sound wierd with that much power in the exhaust. Then spent the night at her friends house and hung out. Today I have Crewing again but this time we meet at 6:00 instead of 5:30 which is better. gotta go, gotta get ready...

Today Has been interesting... First I babysat then went to work but that is not wierd about today. It's the fact that I feel lost and like i'm missing something. I know Melissa Is gone but it doesn't feel like it, but i know once school starts it's going to be horriable. Everyone is going to be crying on the first day back. I don't know if i can take it when we go back. This saturday is the services at 10 Am and I'm going with two of my other friends. It's going to be a hard day for alot of people. I'm scared!! I'm gonna miss not seeing Melissa's beautyful smile and her great personality but life has to go on, we can't live in the past. I hope everyone has thanked god for still being alive because you never know When your going to be NEXT.
